SN	                 Option	                                         Description

1	                   bd	                    The represents the border width. The default width is 2.



2	                   bg	                         It represents the background color of the canvas.



3	                 confine	             It is set to make the canvas unscrollable outside the scroll
                                             region.



4	                 cursor	                  The cursor is used as the arrow, circle, dot, etc. on
                                                                  the canvas.



5	                 height	                It represents the size of the canvas in the vertical direction.



6	             highlightcolor	              It represents the highlight color when the widget is focused.



7	                 relief	                           It represents the type of the border. The possible
                                                          values are SUNKEN, RAISED, GROOVE, and RIDGE.



8	              scrollregion	                     It represents the coordinates specified as the tuple
                                                                 containing the area of the canvas.



9	                 width	                                  It represents the width of the canvas.



10	           xscrollincrement	                          If it is set to a positive value. The canvas
                                                          is placed only to the multiple of this value.



11	            xscrollcommand	                          If the canvas is scrollable, this attribute
                                                    should be the .set() method of the horizontal scrollbar.



12	            yscrollincrement	             Works like xscrollincrement, but governs vertical movement.



13	            yscrollcommand	                        If the canvas is scrollable, this attribute
                                                     should be the .set() method of the vertical scrollbar.